To save a string as a file in MATLAB, you can use the `fprintf` function. Here's an example:

```matlab
% Define the string
myString = 'Hello, world! This is a test file.';

% Open a new file for writing
fileID = fopen('myFile.txt', 'w');

% Write the string to the file
fprintf(fileID, '%s', myString);

% Close the file
fclose(fileID);
```

This will create a new file called `myFile.txt` in the current working directory, containing the string `Hello, world! This is a test file.`

You can also use other file formats if required such as .csv, .txt, .dat or .xlsx etc, by changing the extension in the filename in the function `fopen()`. You can then open this file in a text editor to view and edit the content of the file.
